-- RealD Plans to Cut 20% of Employees as 3-D Installs Slow
-- B y   R o b   G o l u m
-- 2013-11-01T21:31:37Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-11-01/reald-plans-to-cut-20-of-employees-as-3-d-installs-slow.html
RealD Inc. (RLD) , a provider of 3-D
technology to cinemas, plans to cut 20 percent of its jobs as a
result of slowing installations.  The company, based in Beverly Hills, California, plans to
record costs of $3.8 million to $4.1 million over the remaining
two quarters of its 2014 fiscal year, according to a  regulatory
filing  today.  RealD had 163 employees at the end of March, according to
data compiled by Bloomberg. The company said the 3-D business is
maturing in several markets.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Rob Golum at 
 rgolum@bloomberg.net  